==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Workman
<hw>Work"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Workmen</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[AS.
<ets>weorcmann</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A man employed in labor, whether in tillage or
manufactures; a worker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, especially, a skillful artificer or
laborer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Workmanlike</ent>⟦br⟧
